<h1>Example 2</h1>

<section>
	<p class="example-intro">Coordinating conjunctions don't always call for commas. In situations when their is no independent clause following the coordinating conjunction, a comma is not necessary and should be omitted.</p>
</section>

<section>
	<h4 class="example example-sentence example-example">The system had been implemented to track the outcomes of the different treatment methods<span class="red">, and</span> the frequency with which they occured.</h4>
	<p class="example example-explanation example-explanation">This sentence provides an unnecessary comma before the coordinating conjunction, "and." The clause following "and", "the frequency with which they occured, is not an independent clause because it lacks a verb. When we don't have an independent clause following our coordinating conjunction, we should omit the comma.</p>
	<h4 class="example example-corrected example-corrected">The system had been implemented to track the outcomes of different treatment methods and the frequency with which they occured.</h4>
	<p class="example corrected-explanation example-corrected-explanation">The sentence is now correct. We simply removed the comma before the coordinating conjunction, "and." Whenever you see a coordinating conjunction, you should ask yourself if it is followed by an independent clause. If it is, then you need to use a comma before it.</p>
	<button class="btn btn-large btn-primary example-button">Show Example</button>
</section>

<section>
	<h4 class="example example-sentence example-example">The attending physician asked the nurse to check the patient's oxygen levels<span class="red">, and</span> perform a blood-gas analysis.</h4>
	<p class="example example-explanation example-explanation">Once again we see a comma used to join two object clauses. Because the clause "perform a blood-gas analysis" is not an independent clause (it lacks a subject), we should omit the comma before the coordinating conjunction, "and."</p>
	<h4 class="example example-corrected example-corrected">The attending physician asked the nurse to check the patient's oxygen levels <span class="green">and</span> perform a blood-gas analysis.</h4>
	<p class="example corrected-explanation example-corrected-explanation">By removing the comma before the coordinating conjunction, "and," we are able to correct our sentence.</p>
	<button class="btn btn-large btn-primary example-button">Show Example</button>
</section>

